    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1995 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) is a superlative example of the front-midship, rear-wheel-drive icon. The 13B-REW power plant maintains exceptional compression across all rotor faces, with the sequential twin-turbochargers providing a seamless boost transition at 4,500 RPM. The chassis remains factory-spec, featuring the original double-wishbone suspension and four-piston aluminum calipers that provide surgical feedback. Every bushing is pliable, and the vacuum lines have been preemptively refreshed with high-temp silicone to ensure the integrity of the complex solenoid rack. The exterior retains its original high-depth finish, and the interior is free of the typical UV degradation seen in this generation. This is a turn-key, investment-grade rotary for the discerning enthusiast who demands mechanical perfection.",
